  "algorithm_summary": "This prognostic survival model uses Cox proportional hazard regression to predict the risk of being prescribed warfarin, clopidogrel, or statins within 1-5 years. The model includes two variants: a BMI model (when height and weight are available) and a weight model (when only weight is available). Predictors include demographics (age, weight/BMI, gender, race) and clinical variables identified by ICD-9 codes (diabetes, coronary disease, atrial fibrillation, hypertension, atherosclerosis, CHF, previous clot, dialysis). Each diagnostic variable requires 2 instances of relevant ICD-9 codes at baseline. The model converts linear predictors to exposure risk probabilities at specific time points using baseline survival functions from the Breslow estimator.",
